-- 
U.S. Secretly Funded Syrian Opposition, Washington Post Reports

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-04-18T06:03:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/u-s-secretly-funded-syrian-opposition-washington-post-reports.html
The U.S. State Department secretly
funded Syrian opposition groups and projects including an anti-
government satellite television channel, the Washington Post
reported, citing classified diplomatic cables disclosed by the
website WikiLeaks.   Payments included as much as $6 million to the London-based
Syrian exile group Movement for Justice and Development to
operate Barada TV and other activities, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Kraus at 
 jkraus2@bloomberg.net  